---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-spain', text: 'Why Retirees Choose Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-options', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Cost Planning', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Spain Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/spain/insurance' },
  { title: 'Portugal for Retirees', href: '/insurance-for/retirees/in/portugal' },
  { title: 'European Families Abroad', href: '/best/european-families-abroad' },
  { title: 'Pre-Existing Conditions', href: '/best/pre-existing-conditions-insurance' },
  { title: 'Italy for Retirees', href: '/insurance-for/retirees/in/italy' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'ageLimit', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'nlvAccepted', header: 'NLV Accepted' },
  { key: 'spainNetwork', header: 'Spain Network' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly (Age 60)' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', ageLimit: '74', nlvAccepted: 'Yes', spainNetwork: 'Excellent', monthly: '$320-480' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', ageLimit: '74', nlvAccepted: 'Yes', spainNetwork: 'Excellent', monthly: '$300-450' },
  { provider: 'Sanitas (Bupa Spain)', ageLimit: '69', nlvAccepted: 'Yes', spainNetwork: 'Excellent', monthly: '$180-350' },
  { provider: 'Adeslas', ageLimit: '65', nlvAccepted: 'Yes', spainNetwork: 'Excellent', monthly: '$150-300' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'item', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'notes', header: 'Notes' },
];

const costRows = [
  { item: 'International Insurance (55-59)', monthly: '$260-380', notes: 'Meets NLV requirements' },
  { item: 'International Insurance (60-64)', monthly: '$320-480', notes: 'Meets NLV requirements' },
  { item: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$420-620', notes: 'Meets NLV requirements' },
  { item: 'Spanish Private Insurance', monthly: '$150-350', notes: 'Local coverage only' },
  { item: 'Public Healthcare (after residency)', monthly: '$60-100', notes: 'Convenio especial' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Retirees in Spain | Non-Lucrative Visa Guide 2026"
  description="Complete guide to health insurance for Americans and Brits retiring in Spain. Non-Lucrative Visa requirements, insurance options, costs, and healthcare access."
  headline="Health Insurance for Retirees in Spain"
  subheadline="Spain offers sunshine, culture, and excellent healthcare at European prices. The Non-Lucrative Visa makes it accessible—but has strict insurance requirements. Here's what you need."
  heroImage="/images/countries/spain-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Spain Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna"
>
  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mb-4">
    <strong>Affiliate disclosure:</strong> We may earn a commission when you click our links and purchase insurance. This doesn't affect our recommendations or the price you pay.
  </p>

  <h2 id="overview" class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Overview</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">
    Spain has long attracted retirees from northern Europe and increasingly from North America. The combination of Mediterranean climate, rich culture, excellent food, affordable living, and world-class healthcare makes it a compelling choice. For non-EU citizens, the Non-Lucrative Visa (NLV) is the primary path to retirement residency.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    Spain has some of the strictest insurance requirements in Europe. Your policy must meet specific criteria, and not all international insurers qualify. This guide covers what works—and what doesn't.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Key Facts for Retirees</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Visa:</strong> Non-Lucrative Visa (no work permitted)</li>
      <li><strong>Insurance required:</strong> Yes—strict requirements</li>
      <li><strong>Healthcare quality:</strong> Ranked 7th globally (WHO)</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of living:</strong> 30-40% lower than UK/US</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> 300+ sunny days in southern regions</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="why-spain" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Why Retirees Choose Spain</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Mediterranean Lifestyle</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Long lunches, late dinners, afternoon siestas, and a culture that prioritizes quality of life. Spain offers the European lifestyle many retirees dream of. The slower pace, outdoor living, and social culture contribute to longevity—Spain has one of the highest life expectancies in the world.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Excellent Healthcare</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Spain's healthcare system ranks 7th globally. Public hospitals are excellent; private options are affordable. Medical costs are a fraction of US prices. Whether you use public or private care, you're in good hands.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Affordable Living</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Outside major cities and tourist hotspots, Spain is affordable. Andalusia, Valencia region, and inland areas offer comfortable retirement on $2,000-3,000/month. Even Barcelona and Madrid cost less than comparable US or UK cities.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Established Expat Communities</h3>
  <p class="mb-6">
    The Costa del Sol, Costa Blanca, and Balearic Islands have large English-speaking communities. Finding English-speaking doctors, services, and social connections is straightforward. You can integrate as much or as little as you choose.
  </p>

  <h2 id="visa-options" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Visa Options</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Non-Lucrative Visa (NLV)</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    The main visa for retirees. Requires proving income of approximately €2,400/month (€28,800/year) without working. Pension, Social Security, investment income all qualify. Initial visa is 1 year, renewable for 2-year periods. After 5 years, can apply for permanent residency.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Golden Visa</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Alternative for those with €500,000+ to invest in Spanish real estate. Provides residency without income requirements. No minimum stay requirement. More expensive but more flexible for those with capital.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">EU Citizens</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    EU citizens don't need visas—they have right of residence. Register with local authorities after 3 months. Can access public healthcare through EU coordination. Post-Brexit, UK citizens now need NLV like other non-EU nationals.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Insurance Is Critical</h3>
  <p class="mb-6">
    NLV applications require comprehensive health insurance. Spain is strict: policies must have no copays, no coverage limits, and include all medical areas. Many international policies don't qualify. Use insurers experienced with Spanish requirements.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Applying for Non-Lucrative Visa?"
    description="Get insurance that meets Spain's strict requirements. Not all policies qualify."
    buttonText="Get NLV-Compliant Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">NLV Insurance Requirements</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Spain requires health insurance that: has no copays or deductibles for covered services, has no annual or lifetime coverage limits (or very high limits), covers all medical specialties, is valid in Spain for the visa duration, and is from an insurer authorized to operate in Spain or with a Spanish partner.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">What Qualifies</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong>Spanish private insurers:</strong> Sanitas (Bupa Spain), Adeslas, MAPFRE, Asisa—these always qualify. <strong>International insurers with Spain experience:</strong> Cigna Global, Allianz Care—they know Spanish requirements and provide compliant policies. Some consulates are stricter than others; Madrid tends to be most demanding.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">What Often Doesn't Qualify</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Travel insurance (too limited). US-based insurance without Spanish authorization. Policies with high deductibles or copays. Plans with annual coverage limits under €30,000. SafetyWing and similar nomad insurance. When in doubt, use Spanish insurers or established international providers.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">After Residency: Convenio Especial</h3>
  <p class="mb-6">
    After legal residency, you can apply for "convenio especial"—access to Spanish public healthcare for approximately €60-100/month (higher if over 65). This provides full access to Spain's excellent public system. Many retirees transition to convenio especial and drop private insurance, or keep private for faster access.
  </p>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Recommended Providers</h2>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Cigna Global — Best International Option</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Experienced with Spanish NLV requirements. Provides documentation that consulates accept. Excellent network throughout Spain with direct billing at major hospitals. Pre-existing conditions covered with guaranteed acceptance. Good for retirees who want worldwide coverage beyond Spain.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Allianz Care — Best European International</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    German-headquartered insurer with strong Spanish network. NLV-compliant policies. Competitive pricing for European coverage. Good choice for retirees planning to travel within Europe or splitting time between countries.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Sanitas (Bupa Spain) — Best Spanish Insurer</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Bupa's Spanish subsidiary. Extensive network throughout Spain. Always accepted for NLV applications. Competitive pricing, especially for Spain-only coverage. Age limit 69 for new applicants. Excellent choice for retirees settling permanently in Spain.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Adeslas — Best Value Spanish</h3>
  <p class="mb-6">
    Spain's largest private insurer. Extensive network. Lower premiums than international options. Age limit 65 for new applicants (a limitation). Spain-only coverage. Great value if you qualify by age and don't need coverage outside Spain.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Not Sure Which Insurer?"
    description="Spanish NLV requirements are strict. Get quotes from insurers that definitely qualify."
    buttonText="Get Compliant Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <h2 id="healthcare-system" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Healthcare System</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Public Healthcare</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Spain's public system is excellent—ranked 7th globally. Modern facilities, well-trained staff, comprehensive coverage. After obtaining residency and convenio especial, you access this system for €60-100/month. Care is free at point of service.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Private Healthcare</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Private hospitals offer faster access, private rooms, and English-speaking staff. Costs are reasonable by international standards. With private insurance, you avoid public system wait times while maintaining choice of doctors and facilities.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Regional Differences</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    Healthcare is managed regionally. Catalonia, Madrid, and Basque Country have particularly strong systems. Rural areas have fewer specialists—serious conditions may require travel to larger cities. Most retirees settle in areas with excellent healthcare access.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Pharmacies</h3>
  <p class="mb-6">
    Pharmacies are everywhere and well-stocked. Pharmacists can advise on minor conditions. Many medications cheaper than US prices. With public healthcare, prescriptions are subsidized (free for pensioners in some regions).
  </p>

  <h2 id="costs" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Cost Planning</h2>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">Total Healthcare Budget</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    For a 60-year-old retiree: Private insurance ($300-450/month) + out-of-pocket ($30-50/month) = $330-500/month. After convenio especial: Public access ($80/month) + optional private ($0-200/month) + out-of-pocket ($30-50/month) = $110-330/month.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong>Spanish insurer:</strong> Sanitas and Adeslas cost less than international options if you qualify by age. <strong>Transition to convenio especial:</strong> After residency, public access at €60-100/month is excellent value. <strong>Keep private for specific needs:</strong> Some retirees use public for most care, private for specialists or when speed matters.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Compare to Home Country</h3>
  <p class="mb-6">
    US: Healthcare costs $1,200-2,000+/month at age 60-65. UK: NHS is free but limited for non-residents abroad. Spain at $300-500/month for comprehensive coverage represents significant savings while maintaining quality.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
    <div class="border-b pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Will my US insurance qualify for the NLV?</h3>
      <p>Almost certainly not. Spain requires insurers authorized to operate in Spain or with Spanish partners. US domestic insurance doesn't meet this requirement. Use Cigna Global, Allianz Care, or Spanish insurers like Sanitas.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Does SafetyWing work for Spanish visa?</h3>
      <p>No. SafetyWing is travel medical insurance with coverage limits and deductibles. Spain requires comprehensive coverage without these limitations. SafetyWing doesn't meet NLV requirements.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">What is convenio especial?</h3>
      <p>A program allowing legal residents to access Spain's public healthcare system by paying approximately €60-100/month (higher if over 65). Available after obtaining residency. Provides full access to public hospitals and doctors. Many retirees transition to this after their first year.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">I'm over 65—can I still get insurance?</h3>
      <p>Yes, but options narrow. Spanish insurers like Adeslas have age 65 limit. Sanitas accepts up to 69. International insurers like Cigna accept up to 74. Apply before reaching these limits to ensure access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Can I use EHIC/GHIC from UK/EU in Spain?</h3>
      <p>EHIC/GHIC covers emergency care for tourists but doesn't qualify for residency. If you're EU citizen, you can access Spanish healthcare through EU coordination (S1 form). Post-Brexit UK citizens need private insurance for NLV.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b pb-4">
      <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">How strict are consulates about insurance requirements?</h3>
      <p>Very strict, especially Madrid and Barcelona consulates. They verify that policies have no deductibles, no coverage limits, and cover all specialties. Rejections for inadequate insurance are common. Use insurers experienced with Spanish requirements.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Retire in Spain?"
    description="Get NLV-compliant insurance from providers that understand Spanish requirements."
    buttonText="Get Your Spain Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-12">
    This information is for educational purposes. Visa requirements and insurance rules change. Spanish consulates have discretion in applications. Verify current requirements and consider consulting an immigration lawyer. Last updated: April 2026.
  </p>
</PageShell>
